From d7d8227503609581f1e0776eedaadccf01982dc7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Slick <slick@slicksync.local>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 14:20:40 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: poll cycle down to 1 minute (from 5)

activityMonitor's scheduled check now runs every 1 minute instead of
5. sessionTracker's freshness window is a separate, independently
declared constant (not imported/shared) and was deliberately left
unchanged and explicitly commented as such, so this doesn't
accidentally undo the v1.9.26 false-negative fix - Nuvio's
checkpoint-only update cadence means a short freshness window would
reintroduce that bug regardless of how often we poll.

Also explains the Top Watched minutes-watched inaccuracy reported
alongside this request: those numbers come from WatchSession.durationSeconds,
which was being truncated by the exact same v1.9.26 bug (sessions
getting closed after ~1 poll cycle regardless of actual watch time) -
not a separate issue, same root cause.

Bump to 1.9.27, changelog entry added.
---
 client/public/changelog.json    | 10 ++++++++++
 package.json                    |  2 +-
 server/utils/activityMonitor.js |  4 ++--
 server/utils/sessionTracker.js  | 10 +++++++++-
 4 files changed, 22 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

